Poem; transcribed in Nakata and Fu, Masterpieces, vol. 2, p. 140.
   On festival days of the four seasons people busily hurry;
   From this one knows we are living in a happy domain.
   The ninth day [of the month] approaches, yet beside the fence is lonely;
   Only when the chrysanthemums blossom will the Ch’ung-yang Festival arrive. 
– trans. By R. Harrist
